{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772182376,"nonce":"SQFVehVfP0i8WcIm7lfdFdFGhEc=","title":"Separate Verwaltung links into global and department-scoped sections","message":"The /verwaltung page currently renders all management links in a single flat list. This mixes two different scopes:\n\n**Cross-department (global) actions:**\n- \"Werkstätten verwalten\" (departments_path) — manages ALL departments\n\n**Current-department actions:**\n- \"Artikel anlegen\" — creates items in current department\n- \"Verleihende verwalten\" — manages staff in current department\n- \"Werkstattinfos bearbeiten\" — edits current department\n- \"Werkstatt vorübergehend schließen/öffnen\" — toggles current department staffed status\n- \"Rechtstexte bearbeiten\" — edits legal texts for current department\n- \"Statistik\" — stats for current department\n\n**Proposed:** Split the .mgmt-links area into two visually distinct sections:\n1. First: cross-department section containing \"Werkstätten verwalten\" (and future cross-department links)\n2. Second: current-department section with all department-scoped links\n\nThis makes it clear which actions affect the current department vs. the entire system.\n\nNote: members see \"Werkstattinfos bearbeiten\" instead of \"Werkstätten verwalten\" — they would have no global section (hide it or show empty).\n\nRelated: 7248057 (broader nav redesign) may subsume this, but this is a small self-contained improvement.","files":null}]}